Template-Type: ReDIF-Paper 1.0
Handle: RePEc:btb:wpaper:001
Title: Optimal Transfer Design in Post-Scarcity Economies: Creative Currency Octaves and Public Trust Foundations as Incentive-Compatible Welfare
Author-Name: Duke Johnson
Creation-Date: 2025-07-31
Abstract: This paper explores the mathematical and social design of the Creative Currency Octaves (CCO) framework. It posits that traditional welfare models fail in post-scarcity transitions and proposes an incentive-compatible system utilizing Public Trust Foundations (PTF) to ensure equitable resource distribution without stifling innovation.
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/pdfs/optimal-transfer-design.pdf
File-Format: Application/pdf
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/optimal-transfer-design.html
File-Format: text/html
Classification-JEL: D63, H53, E42
Keywords: dual currency, welfare economics, mechanism design, post-scarcity

Template-Type: ReDIF-Paper 1.0
Handle: RePEc:btb:wpaper:002
Title: Dual Currency Systems and Inflation: CCO's Price Stability Mechanisms
Author-Name: Duke Johnson
Creation-Date: 2025-08-15
Abstract: An analysis of how a dual-currency system (Basics and Credits) within the CCO framework prevents hyperinflation and ensures price stability for essential goods. The paper details the algorithmic adjustments required to maintain purchasing power parity across different economic 'octaves.'
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/pdfs/dual-currency-inflation.pdf
File-Format: Application/pdf
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/dual-currency-inflation.html
File-Format: text/html
Classification-JEL: E31, E42
Keywords: inflation, dual currency, monetary stability

Template-Type: ReDIF-Paper 1.0
Handle: RePEc:btb:wpaper:003
Title: Economic Modeling and Simulation Analysis of Creative Currency Octaves
Author-Name: Duke Johnson
Creation-Date: 2025-08-20
Abstract: Using agent-based modeling, this paper simulates the long-term viability of the CCO model. It tests various stress scenarios, including rapid automation and resource scarcity, to demonstrate the robustness of the proposed conversion rates and capacity limits.
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/pdfs/economic-modeling-simulation.pdf
File-Format: Application/pdf
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/economic-modeling-simulation.html
File-Format: text/html
Classification-JEL: C63, D58
Keywords: simulation, agent-based modeling, economic systems

Template-Type: ReDIF-Paper 1.0
Handle: RePEc:btb:wpaper:004
Title: Creative Currency Octaves and Public Trust Foundations: Integrated Framework
Author-Name: Duke Johnson
Creation-Date: 2025-08-25
Abstract: This foundational document describes the interplay between CCO (the currency mechanism) and PTF (the institutional mechanism). It outlines a roadmap for transitioning from market-based capitalism to a compassion-oriented economic structure.
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/pdfs/cco-ptf-integrated-framework.pdf
File-Format: Application/pdf
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/cco-ptf-integrated-framework.html
File-Format: text/html
Classification-JEL: D47, L31
Keywords: nonprofit economics, system integration

Template-Type: ReDIF-Paper 1.0
Handle: RePEc:btb:wpaper:005
Title: Cultural Value Integration in Economic Systems: The CCO Framework
Author-Name: Duke Johnson
Creation-Date: 2025-08-20
Abstract: Examining the intersection of culture and economics, this paper proposes methods for quantifying and incentivizing cultural contributions through the CCO framework, ensuring that artistic and social value is recognized alongside traditional labor.
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/pdfs/cultural-value-integration.pdf
File-Format: Application/pdf
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/cultural-value-integration.html
File-Format: text/html
Classification-JEL: Z1, D63
Keywords: cultural economics, value systems

Template-Type: ReDIF-Paper 1.0
Handle: RePEc:btb:wpaper:006
Title: Integrated Digital Governance and Economic Innovation: CIP-CCO-PTH-SZH Framework
Author-Name: Duke Johnson
Creation-Date: 2025-08-28
Abstract: A comprehensive overview of the four pillars of the proposed framework: Citizens Internet Portal (CIP), Creative Currency Octaves (CCO), Public Trust Housing (PTH), and Social Zone Harmonization (SZH). It argues for a unified digital architecture to manage these systems.
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/pdfs/integrated-digital-governance.pdf
File-Format: Application/pdf
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/integrated-digital-governance.html
File-Format: text/html
Classification-JEL: H11, O38
Keywords: governance, digital systems

Template-Type: ReDIF-Paper 1.0
Handle: RePEc:btb:wpaper:007
Title: Citizens Internet Portal: Structural Incorruptibility Through Distributed Democratic Architecture
Author-Name: Duke Johnson
Creation-Date: 2025-12-29
Abstract: This paper details the technical specifications of the CIP, a platform designed to facilitate direct democracy and transparent resource management. It focuses on the use of distributed ledger technology to ensure the system remains resistant to central corruption.
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/pdfs/citizens-internet-portal.pdf
File-Format: Application/pdf
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/citizens-internet-portal.html
File-Format: text/html
Classification-JEL: D72, H11
Keywords: democracy, digital governance

Template-Type: ReDIF-Paper 1.0
Handle: RePEc:btb:wpaper:008
Title: Democratic Governance in Economic Systems: Lessons from Public Trust Housing
Author-Name: Duke Johnson
Creation-Date: 2025-08-30
Abstract: Analyzing the governance structures of housing cooperatives and trusts, this paper proposes a refined model for PTH that balances individual autonomy with community-wide sustainability and affordability.
