Template-Type: ReDIF-Paper 1.0
Handle: RePEc:btb:wpaper:011
Title: Transforming the US Real Estate Market Through Public Trust Housing
Author-Name: Duke Johnson
Creation-Date: 2025-08-25
Abstract: A focused look at the application of PTH in the United States. It outlines how de-commodifying a significant portion of the housing stock can stabilize the economy and eliminate homelessness while maintaining a secondary market for Credits-based real estate.
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/pdfs/us-real-estate-transformation.pdf
File-Format: Application/pdf
File-URL: https://bettertobest.github.io/research-hub/papers/us-real-estate-transformation.html
File-Format: text/html
Classification-JEL: R31, G21
Keywords: housing, real estate

Template-Type: ReDIF-Paper 1.0
Handle: RePEc:btb:wpaper:012
Title: Community-Based Monetary Innovation for Development
Author-Name: Duke Johnson
Creation-Date: 2025-08-18
Abstract: Exploring the role of localized CCO implementations in developing nations. The paper argues that dual-currency systems can protect local economies from global market volatility while fostering internal community development.
